					<description><![CDATA[<p>Series B funding supports factory expansion Senra Systems has raised $65 million in Series B funding to scale its software-driven manufacturing platform for wire harness production. The investment will support</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/senra-systems-raises-65-million-wire-harness-manufacturing/" data-wpel-link="internal">Senra Systems Raises $65 Million to Expand Aerospace Manufacturing Capacity</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Series B funding supports factory expansion</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Senra Systems has raised $65 million in Series B funding to scale its software-driven manufacturing platform for wire harness production. The investment will support the opening of a third factory as the company works to address growing demand from the aerospace and defence sectors.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding round was co-led by Lowercarbon Capital and Interlagos, with participation from General Catalyst, Sequoia Capital, Andreessen Horowitz, Founders Fund, 8VC, CIV, Dylan Field, The Friedkin Group, Jaws Estates Capital, Sozo Ventures and Alumni Ventures.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Chief Executive Officer and co-founder Jordan Black said wire harnesses remain one of the most overlooked </span><a href="https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/bottleneck" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">bottlenecks</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> in aerospace and defence manufacturing despite serving as critical components across advanced aircraft, satellites, launch vehicles and defence systems.</span></p>
<h2><b>Software platform modernises wire harness production</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Senra manufactures complex wire harness systems that distribute power, communications and data throughout aerospace and defence platforms. The platform reduces manual processes, accelerates onboarding and improves manufacturing consistency.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Its manufacturing operations are powered by Amp, the company&#8217;s proprietary software platform that integrates engineering, quoting, supply chain management, production planning and manufacturing workflows into a unified digital system.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Earlier this year, Senra opened its second manufacturing facility in Cypress, increasing its production footprint fivefold. The 80,000-square-foot site is expected to help the company expand monthly production capacity from around 1,000 wire harnesses to approximately 10,000 by next year.</span></p>
<h2><b>Addressing workforce and defence supply chain challenges<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_203573" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203573" class="size-full wp-image-203573" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/a-futuristic-poster-showcasing-a-mesmeri_GDWek4CvXZKXx-qh3GyVaA_4Fj7Tqo_RbiqfXIsUuCBew-1.png" alt="A neon futuristic visual showing automated manufacturing systems producing complex aerospace components." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-203573" class="wp-caption-text">Senra advances software-driven manufacturing to scale production and address workforce and supply chain challenges. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Demand for wire harnesses has increased significantly as governments invest more heavily in aerospace and defence programmes. However, the industry continues to face workforce shortages and manufacturing constraints.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Senra aims to address these challenges by combining software automation with structured workforce training programmes. It is building an integrated manufacturing solution capable of supporting aerospace, defence, energy and computing industries.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Lowercarbon Capital General Partner Caie Kelley said wire harnesses underpin virtually every advanced electronic platform, making manufacturing automation essential for expanding industrial capacity.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/oak-raises-60m-ai-identity-operating-system/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Oak Raises $60M to Build AI-Native Identity Security Platform</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Leadership strengthens growth strategy</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company strengthened its executive team by appointing Ken Venner as Chief Technology and Product Officer. Venner previously served as Chief Information Officer at SpaceX, overseeing enterprise systems and manufacturing infrastructure development. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">He led technology supporting SpaceX&#8217;s production operations and launch infrastructure across multiple advanced aerospace programmes. At Senra, Venner will oversee the company&#8217;s manufacturing platform, operational systems, and long-term technology roadmap. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">He will guide technology strategy as the company prepares for its next phase of business expansion. The company believes software, automation, and workforce development will strengthen domestic manufacturing capacity across critical industries. </span></p>
